Various elected officials, business leaders, and advocacy groups have expressed support for the U.S-Korea Trade Agreement. They believe that the agreement will expand American exports, create jobs, strengthen ties with South Korea, and enhance economic and national security. The business community, including companies like Ford, GE, Boeing, and JPMorgan Chase, sees the agreement as an opportunity to increase market access and promote economic growth. Advocacy groups, such as the Emergency Committee for American Trade and the National Association of Manufacturers, view the agreement as a way to boost American businesses and create new economic opportunities. Overall, these statements of support highlight the potential benefits of the U.S-Korea Trade Agreement for various sectors of the economy.